      • refresh

        public void refresh()
             throws java.io.IOException
        Refreshes the session.

        Logs out and then logs in again. If this works the RequestManager gets refreshed. Throws IOException if an IO Exception occurs or LoginException (which extends from IOException) if login fails

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an IO Exception occurs
        Since:
        1.0

      • login

        public static Session login(java.lang.String username,
                            java.lang.String password,
                            java.lang.String server,
                            java.lang.String schoolName,
                            java.lang.String userAgent)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        Logs in to the server.

        Send an login request to the server and returns Session if the login was successful. Throws IOException if an IO Exception occurs or LoginException (which inherits from IOException) if login fails

        Parameters:
        server - the server from your school as URL
        schoolName - school name of the school you want to connect to
        username - the username used for the API
        password - the password used for the API
        userAgent - the user agent you want to send with
        Returns:
        a Session session
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an IO Exception occurs
        Since:
        1.0
